{"id": "948", "instruction": "A particle moves along a straight line marked with integers. The probability of moving from point $i$ to $i-1$ in one step is $p$, the probability of staying at point $i$ is $q$, and the probability of moving to point $i+1$ is $r$, with $p+q+r=1$. Find the one-step transition probability matrix and the two-step transition probability matrix.\n\nOptions:\nA. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-2}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\2p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\pq\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2+pr\\:,&j=i\\\\rq\\:,&j=i+1\\\\r^2\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nB. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{p,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\2pq+r\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2\\:,&j=i\\\\2pr\\:,&j=i+1\\\\0\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nC. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\2pq\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2+2pr\\:,&j=i\\\\2rq\\:,&j=i+1\\\\r^2\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nD. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\2pq+r\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2\\:,&j=i\\\\pr+2r^2\\:,&j=i+1\\\\0\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+1\\end{cases}$$\nE. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\r^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\2pq\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2\\:,&j=i\\\\2pr+2qr\\:,&j=i+1\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nF. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\pq+2r^2\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2+pr\\:,&j=i\\\\2qr\\:,&j=i+1\\\\0\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nG. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{r,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\p^2+rq\\:,&j=i-2\\\\0\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2\\:,&j=i\\\\2pr\\:,&j=i+1\\\\r^2\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nH. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-3\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\pq+rq\\:,&j=i-1\\\\q^2+pr\\:,&j=i\\\\r^2\\:,&j=i+1\\\\0\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nI. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{p,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-2\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\pq\\:,&j=i-1\\\\2q^2\\:,&j=i\\\\r^2+2pr\\:,&j=i+1\\\\0\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$\nJ. $$\nP^{(1)}=\\left\\{\\begin{matrix} {{0,}} & {{j < i-1}} \\\\ {{q,}} & {{j=i-1}} \\\\ {{r,}} & {{j=i}} \\\\ {{p,}} & {{j=i+1}} \\\\ {{0,}} & {{j > i+1}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right.\n$$\n$$P^{(2)}=\\begin{cases}0\\:,&j<i-1\\\\p^2\\:,&j=i-2\\\\2pq\\:,&j=i-1\\\\r^2+2pr\\:,&j=i\\\\q^2\\:,&j=i+1\\\\0\\:,&j=i+2\\\\0\\:,&j>i+2\\end{cases}$$", "output": "C"}
